    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "could it be nitrogen? i think i heard something about that before. how do i tell if it's specifically a nitrogen thing and not just water? also what should i do about the soil ph if it's off?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nitrogen deficiency usually shows up as uniform yellowing across the older, lower leaves first, while the veins often remain green. To differentiate it from watering issues, feel the soil; if it's soggy, it's likely waterlogged, not just low on nutrients. If you suspect a pH issue, you can purchase a soil test kit, which will tell you the precise acidity or alkalinity of your growing medium. Adjusting the pH can be done with elemental sulfur to lower it or lime to raise it.",
      "source": "target",
