    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. one more thing, i've been trying to keep my compost bin balanced but it seems like the nutrients just disappear sometimes. it feels like the soil is just being stripped of everything good. is there a way to stop that from happening?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like your soil might be experiencing nutrient leaching, which is common, especially with heavy watering. To prevent this, you need to build more stable, slow-release organic matter into your soil. Regularly incorporating aged compost, worm castings, or aged manure helps keep nutrients locked up in the soil structure, preventing them from washing away. Think of it like building a reservoir for your plant's food supply.",
      "source": "target",
